'''Monroe Township''' is one of thirteen [[Civil township|townships]] in [[Washington County, Indiana|Washington County]], [[Indiana]], [[United States|USA]].  As of the [[United States Census, 2000|2000 census]], its population was 615<ref>[http://factfinder.census.gov/servlet/DTTable?_bm=y&-context=dt&-ds_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U&-mt_name=DEC_2000_SF1_U_P001&-CONTEXT=dt&-tree_id=4001&-all_geo_types=N&-geo_id=06000US1817550508&-search_results=01000US&-format=&-_lang=en United States Census Bureau American FactFinder]</ref>.

==Geography==
According to the [[United States Census Bureau]], Monroe Township covers an area of 38.86 square miles (100.65 square kilometers); of this, 38.44 square miles (99.56 square kilometers, 98.92 percent) is land and 0.42 square miles (1.09 square kilometers, 1.08 percent) is water.

